alaxy Z Flip\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\"}, {\"begin\": 2557, \"end\": 2564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0145804755603644e-13, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999973597508254, \"rank\": 2.6230311892464947e-06, \"text\": \"Team France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2658, \"end\": 2668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999989295247, \"rank\": 1.0704818935517578e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2791, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0145804755603644e-13, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, for the first time in the history of the Olympic and Paralympic Games history, a smartphone will be present on the podium.The usual rules state that athletes can not bring personal belongings, such as phones, to the ceremony.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, traditionally, the podium was always photographed by accredited media from afar.However, this year, for the first time in history, the IOC will allow athletes to bring their phones, i.e., the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition, to the Paris 2024 podium, where they will take selfies and upload them in real-time to the official Athlete365 app.There is no sign that Samsung will ever sell this exclusive phone to the general public.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3278, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3047884197374671e-16, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Galaxy Z Flip\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\"}, {\"begin\": 3375, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999989295247, \"rank\": 1.0704818935517578e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3505, \"end\": 3512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0145804755603644e-13, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But if you are not an Olympian, you can at least pre-order the standard Galaxy Z Flip 6.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3594, \"end\": 3602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999381544, \"rank\": 5.993146914763798e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not offer free beverages and transport passes through the Wallet app but boasts the same Galaxy AI capabilities and fantastic design.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, everyone will be able to have a look at the device from July 12, once it is displayed at select locations, including theOlympic Rendezvous Champs-Elysees 125 Experience StoreSamsung opened in April.Samsung, in collaboration with the IOC (International Olympic Committee) and IPC (International Paralympic Committee), will give athletes a head start by gifting them the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition early, on July 18, before the standard model goes on sale on July 24.There is a good reason for this early access, as this year, Samsung's exclusive Olympic Edition phone will play a much bigger role than any of its predecessors.What's different about the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition?By giving athletes early access to the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition, Samsung intends to help them on their journey in Paris.Galaxy AIis at the forefront of the user experience, and Samsung hopes that athletes will find features like Live Translation, Interpreter, and Composer useful.In addition, athletes will benefit from 100GB 5G data from Orange, which will be preloaded on an eSIM, and two years of global warranty.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 4925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4046, \"end\": 4049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3047884197374671e-16, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4051, \"end\": 4082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter