the standard Galaxy Z Flip 6.\", \"from\": 20344, \"to\": 20432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20366, \"end\": 20374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999381544, \"rank\": 5.993146914763798e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not offer free beverages and transport passes through the Wallet app but boasts the same Galaxy AI capabilities and fantastic design.\", \"from\": 20433, \"to\": 20574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As for the phone itself, Samsung describes the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition as having a striking yellow colorway with Olympic rings and the Paralympic Agitos logo in gold.Our story continues after the Galaxy Z Flip 6 hands-on video\\u2026Aside from the unique finish, Samsung also partnered with Parisian Men's Luxury House Berluti, who designed Team France's official Paris 2024 outfits, to create a FlipSuite Case made from Venezia leather.A first in the Olympic and Paralympic Games historyIn 2024, Samsung went one extra step to make the exclusive Olympic Edition smartphone even more special than ever.\", \"from\": 20576, \"to\": 21180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20601, \"end\": 20608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0145804755603644e-13, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}, {\"begin\": 20623, \"end\": 20636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Galaxy Z Flip\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\"}, {\"begin\": 20730, \"end\": 20736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para